      "quoted_tweet_id": "2049103719405391966",
      "retweeted_tweet_id": null,
      "text": "Now for the REAL story:\nJosé Contreras Diaz, a 30-year-old DACA recipient from the Rio Grande Valley in South Texas, was deported to Honduras in January 2026 despite having valid Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals (DACA) status and no criminal record.\n\nContreras Diaz came to the U.S. at age 8 with his family from Honduras In 2004 during the Bush administration.  \nThey received a REMOVAL ORDER more than two decades ago but the family IGNORED it and it was not ENFORCED by ICE ERO until 2026. \nHe was arrested by ICE agents during a routine immigration check-in appointment in January. \n\nHaving DACA status is no longer an automatic blockade on being deported, the Board of Immigration Appeals BIA has ruled, tossing five hundred thousand of thousands of illegal immigrant “Dreamers” into a new and more complicated situation.  Stay tuned.",
      "text_resolved": "Now for the REAL story:\nJosé Contreras Diaz, a 30-year-old DACA recipient from the Rio Grande Valley in South Texas, was deported to Honduras in January 2026 despite having valid Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals (DACA) status and no criminal record.\n\nContreras Diaz came to the U.S. at age 8 with his family from Honduras In 2004 during the Bush administration.  \nThey received a REMOVAL ORDER more than two decades ago but the family IGNORED it and it was not ENFORCED by ICE ERO until 2026. \nHe was arrested by ICE agents during a routine immigration check-in appointment in January. \n\nHaving DACA status is no longer an automatic blockade on being deported, the Board of Immigration Appeals BIA has ruled, tossing five hundred thousand of thousands of illegal immigrant “Dreamers” into a new and more complicated situation.  Stay tuned.",
